common-utils provides common utility functions for string and Xlsx operations.

To use in your CMake project:

    find_package(common-utils CONFIG REQUIRED)
    target_link_libraries(your-target PRIVATE common-utils::common-utils )

Example usage:

    #include <common-utils/core.h>
    #include <common-utils/xlsx.h>
    using namespace common_utils;
    std::string formatted = Core.stringFormat("  hello world  ");
